1) Change our pets to be able to tank better than a L65 PoTime equipped warrior with full AA's (not gonna happen)
<br />

<br />
2) Fix our charm to better match that of druid/enchanter/necro, add a ton of L64 and under summoned type mobs in a ton of zones, and let us charm solo.  Inherent risks of charm, etc...
<br />

<br />
Again, to reiterate:
<br />

<br />
THEY WILL NOT upgrade our pet to be able to make us solo effectively compared to enchanters, necros, druids, etc.  WILL NOT.  Because it would break so much more, it's not even funny.
<br />

<br />
Upgrading our nukes won't help us solo better.  Hell, the upgrades to our nukes they did give us will just help us die faster on raids...
<br />

<br />
They have repeatedly told us they will NOT give us root and/or snare.  If you want to root something, bust out the earth pet, wait for it to cast, and hope it sticks, call the pet off...bout the best we'll get.
<br />

<br />
So, when folks come up with better suggestions that help mages across the board (soloer, grouper, raider), that's when the devs will take notice.
<br />

<br />
Windfollower - the devs do a good enough job ignoring bugs, broken stuff, and other things in beta to really care about "whining" here on our class boards...They ignore the bad except for the real game-breaking stuff, but they will read some of the good suggestions that are balanced.  Unfortunately, on this thread, there haven't been any - by much of any of us really, because there's too many inherent issues with a lot of the suggestions that don't "break the guidelines".
<br />

<br />
M<br />_________________<br />Marthisdil
