				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">You know, I'm always able to see the light at the end of the tunnel, the glass as half full.
<br />

<br />
Reading this thread, though, with so many excellent points about exactly how diminished our class has become has me down in the dumps badly about EQ and Mages, and I've been enthusiastic about the Class and adapted to change since March of 1999.
<br />

<br />
The last straw was someone's post above when they talked about relative power WITHIN THE CLASS of a change from level 61 to 65.  It's true.  A 61 Mage is nearly equivalent to a 65 Mage.  Forget the other classes.  
<br />

<br />
That fact alone is enough to be very distressing.
<br />

<br />
And, thing is,  that's not the ONLY fact.  There are many, many other superb points being made by concerned Mages here.
<br />

<br />
Really, I don't see any sea change happening with respect to the idea of restoring our pets in the way they must be, in order to make this class truly viable power-wise and, yes, fun-wise again.
<br />

<br />
Very depressing all this.  =(  Time for a small break, I guess.
<br />

<br />
Gnomer</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
