			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Naldari has a good suggestion, up our heals to the point they are meaningful, and will keep a pet alive, with no recast time but the standard 2.5 seconds. Add in the 10% damage mitergation or up it would be nice, and we have a solution that helps all area's of play.
<br />

<br />
If you solo,group or raid the odds are you will heal the pet at times, and a very effiecent heal would be a nice change. Also rememebr Rytan did NOT say that soloing was off the books, he said it was a hard sell.  hard sell is POSSIBLE, if it can be shown why. The constant infighting will never give him the answer to that hard sell, so lets hit a middle ground. Pet heals.
<br />

<br />
I think we all agree our pet should and always have the the mages main defining characterist. If that is so, we should be promoting a way to keep the fully buffed pet alive to do the job for us.
<br />

<br />
A heal of 3000 and 4000 points with a 4-5 second cast time respectively would do that, for the cost of 300-400 mana. As pointed out 400 mana buys a new but unbuffed pet, so 400 mana for a 4000 heal works to keep the fully buffed pet alive and killing. Chaining pets would of course end, and while that is the play style for many mages I think even they would agree if they could use the same mana, but it would keep the current pet alive fully buffed they would use it.
<br />

<br />
With a snare to advoice damage, without a root for the same reason, and no slow, our pets die fast if in combat. Damage mitergation and a damn decent heal may swing the ballance with the other pet casters that slow, or snare back to where we are decent at soloing, and it helps the grouping mage who may need to off tank at times, as well as the raiding mage who may decide I don't need to spend 20 aa's for group buffs I will just heal my pet more effiecently, or do both. it opens up possibilities.
<br />

<br />
Without a slow our pets take a ton more damage than a beastlord pet, and as a necro snare (darkness) kites, they take none, so giving us the heals proposed would help. 
<br />

<br />
Thoughts?
<br />

<br />
Calebe</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
