			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I was playing around today in Akheva and Droga killing light blue mobs nearly non-stop.  these guys give us about 1% AA per kill.  this got me thinking, and please let me know if you guys have similar experiences.
<br />

<br />
I can kill these light blue mobs for about 1% AA per kill with little to no downtime and bring in about 40% AA per hour at 65.  I can also take on dark blue mobs that give about 2% AA per kill with more effort and more downtime and bring in roughly the same 40% AA per hour.  at 65, killing harder mobs nets no difference in solo XP gained.  wouldn't it be something if we could take down those dark blue 2% AA mobs at the same rate we take down those 1% AA mobs?  instead of a paltry 40% per hour, we'd bring in 80% per hour, double what we currently do.  here're my thoughts, from an elemental/recently Time flagged viewpoint.
<br />

<br />
1) solo xp vs group xp.  a good group in pofire at castle 2 with a tank and healer can bring in slightly less than, but close to 2 AA per hour.  a group quadding can bring in more, closer to 3 AA per hour.  now, compare those 2 to 3 AA per hour grouped to the 80% per hour we'd make solo, and apply Rytan's "group xp needs to be more lucrative than solo xp" condition, and I think that certainly applies.
<br />

<br />
2) not game breaking.  we wouldn't need huge pet upgrades to do this.  we're not going to get a pet that can tank PoP mobs because it would break too many aspects of the game.  how then could we double the rate at which we kill those 2% mobs?  it wouldn't take much.  up our mana regen.  the 2 per tic we got after the canni-nerf is not sufficent to the solo mage.  I'm not a numbers guy, so I don't have a number for you, but up it, not on par with necros or anything, but up it so we get mana back just a little faster.  that will let us nuke a little more and heal a little more, without blowing our wad on a handful of mobs.  then implement the pet foci or whatever other changes Rytan wants to make to give the pet more hitpoints and better damage mitigation.  doing something with the heals we get would also help out here, as proposed by Naladini.
<br />

<br />
what do you guys think?  my 1 and 2% numbers are with an epic pet and DPoC, while not exactly "out of the box" magician, prolly pretty standard for most solo mages today.  while it's true that necros and quadders are going to be pulling down more solo xp using their methods, there's nothing we can really do about that short of calling for nerfs, and I really don't think anyone wants to nerf other classes, cause we certainly know how bad it hurts.  80% is double what we currently pull down, which is a significant upgrade.  we wouldn't have to get snare or root or slow or other abilities we've never had.  we wouldn't be soloing in PoP, but we'd have Droga, Chardok B, Hate...the places we have now, but with double the xp, with only small changes made.
<br />

<br />
thoughts?
<br />

<br />
edit: oops forgot to mention that these numbers would naturally go up with higher end focus items like SoAS or CCS, and I don't think that's game-breaking either, considering the end-game mages should be capable of more than the standard mage.  that may go without saying, but I didn't want anyone thinking I wanted to solo the same xp as someone with those better focus items, I expect them to do it better and faster.<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=262804" target="_blank" class="postlink">Master Xarden DeVir</a> - Retired.
<br />
The Magician class is dead.  Long live the Magician!</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
