			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">Druids would cry to daddy Sony if we got 3k, 4k heals, even if they were pet-only. Lol. 
<br />

<br />
I never really understood why we get heals. If you could summon an elemental out of thin air, and you were in a bind, would you summon a new one or try to heal the one thats about to die on you? Plus, healing cuts into our dps, and I think we can all agree (OMG) that we are a dps class, and should try to stay that way. 
<br />

<br />
For reading comprehension: I dont have a problem with the heals suggested, other than I dont think we should have to heal our pets to begin with.</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
Let the druids cry I say, after all we are not healing playter but our own pets. As for us healing over making a new pet, that was true when we had no muzzle, belt, weapons, armour to give our pets. Now that we do, I would think a mage would find a way to heal their pet to full so as not to lose all the advantages they have given their initial pet. Frfom a role play perspective it is not hard to imagine a mage calling forth elemental energy to infuse their pet with that would in effect heal them. You may argue that who says that elemental energy would heal said pet, but that is what we have now with PR. Your pet is infused with elemental energy and it is healed. So SoE has set us on that track.
<br />

<br />
As for heal cuts our DPS and we are a DPS class, that is only partially true, a mage is a pet class first and formost, and that pet is our defense. In a group settng with a main tank our DPS does not suffer as we are not healing, in a raid setting, you may need to heal a pet if PoC wears off, but as you can't chain nuke it isn't as bad, as for a mage traveling it makes sense to heal the pet to defend us. Think of it this way, SoE gives us no defense as our pet is it, as a pure defensive measure healing the pet (and that is why we need a huge heal) with enough hit points that it can tank another 19 or 20 seconds gives us the opportunity to gate, or nuke and heal to win a battle that is now unwinable. It helps us and a damn good idea.
<br />

<br />
Actually this may shock you Chak but I agree with this 100%
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">For reading comprehension: I dont have a problem with the heals suggested, other than I dont think we should have to heal our pets to begin with.</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
Back in the day when EQ was new, there were  no mage pet heal spells, none were needed the pet could survive as the mage nukes to kill mobs in about any zone we ventured into. It would be great to have a pet like that again, but it won't happen we are told, so heals are needed. Though like you I agree it would be great to have a pet like that, it should be what the class is, all about the pet, but it isn't. It was, but alas that is no longer true.
<br />

<br />
Calebe</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
